<title>POLAND: ZYWIEC TO CLOSE BREWERY, LAY OFF WORKERS.</title>
<headline>ZYWIEC TO CLOSE BREWERY, LAY OFF WORKERS.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1996-10-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Polish brewer Zaklady Piwowarskie w Zywcu Zywiec SA (Zywiec) said it would lay off 145 out of its 990 workers following decisions to shut down its Bielsko-Biala brewery and phase out soft-drinks production.</p>
<p>Zywiec said in a statement it had decided to shut down the Bielsko-Biala facility because of its poor technical standard and to move production to its modernised brewery in Zywiec.</p>
<p>It also said the it had decided to stop producing soft drinks from the beginning of 1997 in line with its plan to focus on the core beer production after the expiry of its licencing agreement with Pepsi Cola on December 15, 1996.</p>
<p>The company did not give any details and Zywiec's spokesman declined further comment on the decisions.</p>
